cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.CY, cs.DL, cs.LG 

The paper deals with the problem of permissionless Byzantine consensus, which is a topic in computer security (cs.CR) and distributed computing (cs.DC). It also introduces a new blockchain protocol (cs.CY) and a new consensus mechanism (cs.DL) that surpasses the prior state of the art by four orders of magnitude. The paper also includes a new formal method for reasoning about trust, liveness, and safety (cs.LG).
